message.content:
A cabbage butterfly is a common type of white butterfly that belongs to the family Pieridae.
It is predominantly white in color, with black spots on its wings.
The wingspan of an adult cabbage butterfly can range between 1.5 to 2.75 inches.
It has a thin, almost delicate appearance with slender wings that taper at the ends.
The cabbage butterfly is often found in gardens, fields and meadows, particularly around plants of the Brassica family, including cabbage, broccoli and kale.
It has a relatively short lifespan of only a few weeks.
Cabbage butterflies are known for their distinctive fluttering flight pattern.
